      "writtenOn": "2020-11-09T18:59:57Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Your description is correct. We keep the GrTexture alive (so that it can be reused if the same SkPromiseImageTexture is used to fulfill another SkImage). Since the GrTexture is still alive its release proc is not triggered by ~GrSurface. (FWIW GrResourceCache does not have refs to GrGpuResources, it just decides when to delete them and never deletes them when something else has a ref to them.)\n\nThe GrTexture drops its idle proc helpers when the cache calls \"willRemoveLastRef()\". In GL that will the only ref to the helper and will trigger the call. In other backends additional refs are attached to command buffers referring to the texture, so those have to complete as well.\n\nI\u0027m not sure we need this complexity but I want to explore removing GrTexture caching for promise images separately from this API change.",
      "parentUuid": "9162c61b_3f6430ca",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 46,
        "startChar": 12,
        "endLine": 47,
        "endChar": 99
      },
      "revId": "69e74a4a8d27c5c55889f86fe3d60fe3b2019f8b",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02"
    },
    {
      "unresolved": true,
      "key": {
        "uuid": "24abea9c_519f6a4d",
        "filename": "src/gpu/GrTexture.h",
        "patchSetId": 8
      },
      "lineNbr": 47,
      "author": {
        "id": 5036
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-11-09T19:08:35Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "And just to document everything here. Can a GrTexture go \"idle\" in cache if the SkPromiseImageTexture is still alive? In other words the unique key connected to the SkPromiseImageTexture hasn\u0027t been invalidated yet?\n\nSince once we call the idle proc we are telling the client it is okay (from Skia\u0027s POV) to delete the backend object, I guess I just really want to confirm that calling it means not only is Skia done using it but, the SkPromiseImageTexture must be gone as well. Otherwise we may end up trying to use a cached thing that has been deleted?\n\nIf all the above is true, why can\u0027t we just delete the texture from the cache at this point? Doesn\u0027t seem like we should be able to reuse the texture again after calling the idle proc since we don\u0027t know if the client deleted the object or not.",
      "parentUuid": "e52feb87_d9232213",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 46,
        "startChar": 12,
        "endLine": 47,
        "endChar": 99
      },
      "revId": "69e74a4a8d27c5c55889f86fe3d60fe3b2019f8b",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02"
    },
    {
      "unresolved": true,
      "key": {
        "uuid": "41da948f_48a66d1f",
