      "writtenOn": "2020-11-09T19:50:45Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Okay so the client is in charge of knowing that if it deletes the backend texture that it must no use same SkPromiseImageTexture again. I guess this is fine, just from the clients POV seems a little fragile since there isn\u0027t necessarily a direct connection between the PromiseReleaseProc (i.e. our idle proc) and the SkPromiseImageTexture.\n\nMaybe we can update the comment in SkPromiseImageTexture to describe these connections a bit more. Current it says:\n\n\"Once an instance is returned from a PromiseImageTextureFulfillProc it must remain valid until the corresponding PromiseImageTextureReleaseProc is called.\"\n\nMaybe update this to replace \"it\" with \"the GrBackendTexture\".\n\nThen add something like:\n\nIf PromiseImageTextureReleaseProc is called and the client decides to delete the underlying backend API texture, then they should release their ref to the corresponding SkPromiseImageTexture.",
      "parentUuid": "41da948f_48a66d1f",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 46,
        "startChar": 12,
        "endLine": 47,
        "endChar": 99
      },
      "revId": "69e74a4a8d27c5c55889f86fe3d60fe3b2019f8b",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02"
    },
    {
